.P Product Version     22.14    Cadence Design Systems, Inc. 
.fi
.TH addModulePort  22.14 "Fri Oct 06 02:12:27 2023" 
.SH Name \fBaddModulePort\fR \-  Adds a port or bussed port to a module, specified as a module or a hierarchical instance
.SH Syntax \fBaddModulePort\fR  [-help]<moduleName>   <portName> <portDir>  [-bus <n1>:<n2>]  [-moduleBased] 
.P Adds a port or bussed port to a module, specified as a module or a hierarchical instance. 
.SH Parameters    "\fB-help\fR" Outputs a brief description that includes the type and default information for each addModulePort parameter.  For a detailed description of the command and all of its parameters, use the  man  command:    man addModulePort  "\fB-bus <n1>:<n2>\fR" Adds a bussed port to the module. Specify the bus range (the beginning and end of the bus). Use integers to specify the range.  If the specified bus already exists, tool will do bus bit resizing. The specified bus bit range must be adjacent to the first or the last bit of the existing bus. Also, it must have the same ascending or descending order as the existing bus.  "\fB-moduleBased\fR" Specifies if the port is module based.   "\fB<moduleName>\fR" Specifies the name of a hierarchical instance, or a Verilog module if -moduleBased is specified, to which you want to add a port.  Specify "-" for the top hierarchical instance.   "\fB<portDir>\fR" Specifies the port direction. You can specify the direction as:
.RS  "*" 2 input  "*" 2 output  "*" 2 bidi
.RE   "\fB<portName>\fR" Specifies the name of the port to be added.  The specified <portName> can be a new port name or any of the existing internal net names to which the port will connect in the module. Internal net means net inside the module without connections to any existing port of the module. If the new port name is the same as the existing net name in the module, the net will not connect the port. The new port name will be portName_1. Port Name cannot be the same as any existing port name of the same module.  If a bus port is added, the bit port name cannot be the same as any net name in the module. 
.SH Examples
.RS  "*" 2 The following command creates an input port p1 on instance i1/i2/i3. The port p1 must be a new port name in instance i1/i2/i3. Instance i1/i2/i3 contains no nets name p1:   addModulePort i1/i2/i3 p1 input
.RE
.RS  "*" 2 The following set of commands adds a hierarchical block and then adds a bussed port to the block.   addHierInst -cell i_block -hinst i_block1  addModulePort i_block1 data output -bus 31:0  "*" 2 The following command adds two input bits i1[8] and i1[9] to existing top-level bus port i1[0:7].  addModulePort - i1 input -bus 8:9
.RE 
.SH Related Information
.RS  "*" 2 addHierInst  "*" 2 deleteModulePort
.RE
.P
